The paper discusses the use of Isabelle/jEdit as a general IDE for formal languages defined in user-space and embedded into informal text documents. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper explores the use of formal text delimiters and markers for interpretation, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the PIDE framework, which could also be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
